Oct 4 2009 	Still the best hotel in Vegas	I've been staying at the JW Marriott Las Vegas for about 5 years now, and I try to write a review of the property each time I stay. My recent stay was outstanding--everything was perfect. I love this hotel because everyone is genuinely interested in making your stay as nice as possible. Free valet parking is a nice touch. Room: I won't spend time describing the hotel in detail, because the other reviews do a nice job of that. The rooms include a very nice whirlpool tub and a waterfall shower. You can get a rollaway bed if needed. Try to get a room in the lobby tower. I have never had a bad room there.Pool: Great pool with a waterfall. A little colder than I would typically like, but with the hot weather, it feels good. I wish smoking wasn't allowed by Marriott pools, but there is no smoking in the hotel. Restaurants: I really like the Promenade Cafe in the casino. Great food at reasonable prices. I've never had a bad meal there. Apparently word has spread, because we had a wait for a table for the first time ever this year. Probably because you can get a really good 3-course meal for $7.99. Casino: Small casino, but a fun little place. I learned that they will be renovating the casino over the next year, so that will address some of the previous comments about the casino looking outdated. The casino is not owned by Marriott--it is an outside company.The only cons I can think of are that breakfast is not included anymore for Elite members (just go to the Promenade Cafe for a great breakfast at a good price), and there may now be a resort fee (so inquire about that at check in). I'll be returning as soon as I can!	
