Aug 23 2009 	This hotel just made our stay GREAT!	We visited Las Vegas for a week and had a marvellous time. We quickly realised that if we hadn't picked to stay at the JW, our experience would not have been nearly so good. The hotel has a real resort feel - it is in a peaceful location in Summerlin, maybe 20 minutes from the Strip. This was really important because in temperatures reaching 108F during the day, the wonderful water gardens, the superb pool and the golf setting was just a world away from the crowded strip. We loved going down there at night and either drove ourselves or used the free hotel shuttle but I wouldn't have wanted to stay down there. It would be great if you were just going for a weekend, or possibly in the winter when it wasn't so hot, but not in August. We spent fabulous days around the pool - it felt like a real holiday - and then lived it up down on the Strip at night. Our room was very spacious - two queen sized beds and an enormous bathroom with large spa bath and huge shower. We had a small balcony overlooking the grounds and we were in the main tower. There is a restaurant in the hotel but most of the dining options are in the casino area. We ate a lunch buffet and a dinner buffet (pretty mediocre to be honest) and had breakfast a couple of times. Wouldn't rave about any of them other than they were cheap. Valet parking was free and very speedy. The pool is beautiful with superb beds and a good little snack bar with very quick pool service. We spent a lot of time out there. The only problem was that there were not a lot of umbrellas which was strange but as the hotel wasn't crowded when we were there it was not an issue. The loungers were very comfortable.We ate out in Vegas a lot and attended shows and generally walked around admiring all the glitz and glamour. Really enjoyed the week and wouldn't hesitate to return. We visited many of the Strip hotels and whilst they were very elaborate and exciting, it would have been like staying in a theme park: so noisy, crowded, tour groups constantly moving through, the noise from the casinos which are in the lobbies. The JW is NOTHING like this and that was a blessing for us. If you want to be in the heart of the action 24 hours a day, it won't suit you. If you want to have the best of both worlds, then it is a fantastic choice.	
