Apr 7 2009 	The one thing that could have made my stay at the JW Las Vegas perfect is...	its location!Upon arriving at the hotel, you are greeted by complimentary valet service. At the front desk, at check-in, you are treated like a VIP (the complimentary bottled water is a very nice touch.) Our room was immaculate, as well. (and the bathroom, I felt like we were in a luxury suite!!) Very luxurious, quiet, and comfortable. We ordered room service a few times, and it always came on time and the food was awesome!So what's wrong with this hotel?? Its location about 15 minutes away from the strip (by highway) is a BIG drawback. We were in Las Vegas for a concert at the Hard Rock Hotel and had we realized how far of a drive it would be, we would probably have preferred to stay at the Strip instead. Now, I realize that the location of the hotel is something that cannot be changed, so this is the advice that I would offer. IF you are looking for a one night stay in Las Vegas, will not be visiting the strip, and plan on staying inside the hotel the entire time, then this is your place. There is virtually NO nightlife in the surrounding area as it is located in your typical suburban district.If you are planning on visiting the strip, do yourself a favor, stay on the strip!!I'd definitely stay here again though, but only if on a quick one night stay in Las Vegas.	
