ugh it is optional!), saw Vegas and returned to the hotel.Overall had a superb time, when we come back to Vegas we'll stay here again - its great to be off strip, but, still be able to get into the centre easily. The hotel was lovely, staff really great (ignoring the pool!) and our room was great.To say about what other reviewers mentioned... our air conditioner was silent (though we did have to shut the French windows to run it which was mentioned in our welcome notes).	
Oct 8 2008 	Heaven at the JW Marriott	This is a top-notch hotel off the Strip, yet within easy reach of the Strip and surrounding businesses. Although I rated this an &quot;excellent&quot; stay, I do have some quibbles. Pulling up to the hotel, we learned from a bellman that we had to backtrack to another building for check-in. No big deal, but maybe this could have been handled by the concierge on her phone. Kudos to the bellhop team - those folks were great.Our room was really beautiful, with a lovely view of the eastern horizon. I had no problem with the lack of a flat-screen TV (perhaps there was one?) as these are hugely &quot;anti-green&quot; devices and still only show you the same shows you'd get on any other TV. Housekeeping was outstanding, making no fuss about our bikes being in room. The bathroom was beautiful and beautifully kept. The beds were dressed with soft linens and a plush mattress top. We slept very well!One problem was the noise of the air conditioner. We called for help with this, but the handyman who arrived was only able to tell us how to use it, not how to fix it (it was quite loud). We solved the problem by just leaving it off, which is probably not an option for guests during the summer months.We ate at Shizen - wow! So yummy! We also ate at an in-hotel cafe, which was good food-wise, but bad cigarette-smoke-from-the-casino-wise. We ate at Ceres, and the food was excellent both times, and at brunch, creative while still offering the old standbys. Service was quite good.I agree with another reviewer who found the lack of Wi-Fi annoying. With this quality of hotel and the availability of this service at other accommodations, JW should just make it happen. A boon to all and a plus for visitors - and for the hotel.One caveat: you are about a half hour from the Strip. But that's the beauty of this place.	
