ght and on the same page.Maid service was spotty at best, first two nights received room cleaning, last two nights, nothing, and they didnt show up.I happened to catch a maid in the hallway and asked why my room wasnt cleaned, and I got a &quot;no speak English&quot; response....ok whatever, moving onThey need to update the TV's...most hotels of this star rating has flat screens by now. The bed and the sheets were very comfortable. I happened to look at when the mattress was purchased and it was back in 1999, so maybe a refurbish would be a good idea sometime in the near future.At check out I brought up the problem of mold that was in our shower, they seemed surprised, not sure if they were surprised I brought it up, or it had mold. They made a note of it and said would have it checked out.As I said, this was our anniverery and several other reviews said they were sent, a bottle of champaign, strawberries and chocolates to their room..., no such luck here. Although my travel agent made sure to let the hotel know about the special anniversary celebration the hotel they seemed to just ignore it.The valet service was great; the guys very fast, helpful and friendly.The hotel seemed to do the bulk of their business with convention guests, and this is who they prefer to cater to, very little leisure guests and I can tell the business guest are number one here and treated so, vacationers are a after thought.As I said, I did like the hotel, but it fell short of my expectations.	
