Jun 24 2008 	Great property for thse who have been to Vegas before	We have been to Vegas a few times now and we always stay on the Strip at MGM, Planet Hollywood... but I had once read very nice reviews about this property and I was very curious. This hotel had amazing rooms. First of all the rooms are enormous for hotel rooms, especially when you compare it to the regular rooms at any hotel on the strip. They had amazing bathrooms with his and hers sinks, very nice Jacuzzi tub for two (plenty of space; I must add that my husband and I are tall people) separate stand up shower, and the toilet was in a separate place with a door, very nice. The property had very pretty ground, the valet parking was for free and the crew was really nice and fast, very worth the tip :-) They have a few restaurants in the hotel but we had tried only Ceres for breakfast one morning and the brunch was really nice, must try the waffles, they were wonderful, and I normally don't eat waffles.The hotel service was good, and they also have the Rampart Casino connected to the property for all those late night gamblers, $5 blackjack at the Rampart casino. The grounds were beautiful but we never got to use the pool since the weather did not cooperate for us that week-end ;-( The drive the to strip was only 12 minutes so it was very convenient. The only thing I was not really impressed with was the Spa. It seems that it was only one person doing all the treatments that day, she was nice but nothing spectacular. If you want to use the spa facilities ( which included the fitness area) a they charge you a $25 fee per day ( free day pass to the facilities, if you do a spa service that same day). I would not recommend to pay $25 because it was worth it. I think the hotel should give free access to these facilities anyways.Overall it was an amazing hotel if you want to still enjoy the casinos and dining on the strip but prefer to relax at night and be away from all the noise and rumble.	
