Apr 17 2008 	Very nice resort But Make Sure You Get the Right Room	We really liked this resort and will definitely go back. The restaurants were good, large and well appointed rooms, grounds are lovely, great spa, attentive staff. My one BIG complaint is that my room in the Spa Tower &quot;faced the golf course.&quot; This actually means you can see the golf course waaaayyyy over there on the other side of a busy road. It also looked directly over the entrance way. This meant noise all day and (this being Vegas) well into the wee hours as people returned from their nights out in, shall we say, a cheerful frame of mind PLUS lots of traffic noise from the busy road starting in the early morning. It being nice weather, I would've liked to have slept with my french doors open but this proved absolutely impossible to do and get sleep and I was on the 5th floor! I can only imagine what it would've been like on the second floor! I honestly have to say I've rarely been in such a noisy room and certainly not at $275 a night! When we return, I will definitely make very sure I'm not &quot;facing the golf course&quot; in the Spa Tower! That being said, the resort is great in every other way. I do wish they had some other nightclub venue. They have two small bars offering live entertainment but nothing with a dance floor or a nightclub atmosphere. Also, they have a free shuttle to the strip (otherwise a $40 cab fare including tip); however, it lets you out across from Fashion Mall. It's a real hike from there to any of the main resorts (like at least 20 blocks). Cab fare from there to Mandalay Bay where we were attending a show was $15 with tip. Since we were only going to the Strip once during our stay, it wasn't a big deal. If you are planning to spend a lot of time on the Strip, you might want to take the transportation into consideration.	
