Mar 29 2008 	Great Rooms Great Pool Great Price!	We stayed at the JW Marriott in Summerlin over Easter weekend. The rooms are big and the bathrooms are huge, with double sinks, a separate rain shower, and a tub for 2! We were very comfortable for the 5 nights we stayed. We especially enjoyed the pool area and the beautiful grounds. The price we got was a tremendous value, and there are no hidden fees like resort fees or parking fees. The casino attached to the JW is small but adequate. The hotel does offer a complimentary shuttle to the Strip---just check the times. The hotel breakfast was OK, but we found the Promenade restaurant next to the casino to offer great breakfasts at very reasonable prices. The Irish pub doesn't seem all that authentic, but it does offer some good specials and great Irish beer , and the bread pudding was awesome. The sushi bar was also a favorite with our sushi-loving friends. There are also a couple of other restaurants on the grounds, but we simply ran out of time! There are also many restaurants and shopping located within a couple of miles, so you really don't need to go to the Strip unless you choose to do so. If you want to get away from the Strip, but still enjoy the weather and perhaps some golf and the pool, the JW would be a great choice. It also seemed to be a very family friendly place, and you can feel very safe! When we travel to Las Vegas again, we will definitely consider returning to JW Marriott.	
Feb 23 2008	Loved the JW Marriott	We stayed at the JW Marriott in January after a 3 day stay at the Venetian. We loved both hotels! The JW Marriott is a nice change of pace if you want to get away from the hustle and bustle of the strip. The property is beautiful and the service is excellent. Our room was beautiful, a nice size and very clean. We also had a lovely view of the mountains. Make sure you get a room with a balcony, it does make a difference. The staff does try to please and are very friendly. The casino is also very nice. If you stay at the JW Marriott make sure you eat at Rosemary's. It is only 5 minutes from the hotel and I can see why it is the #1 restaurant in Las Vegas. We also took a tour to the Grand Canyon, South Rim with grand-adventures.com. Daryll was our tour guide/owner. Most of the tours from Las Vegas are to the West Rim, which is actually not in the Grand Canyon National Park. This tour takes you to the South Rim and is really beautiful. The day we went there was a fresh coat of snow and it was breathtaking. Daryll's tours are different in the fact that he only takes about 10 people in a mini van, unlike most tours to the south rim which are in a large bus with 50 passengers. The ride was about 5 hours each way, but well worth the trip. He allows plenty of time at the canyon. I highly recommend this tour if you want to see the South Rim and have a limited amout of time. We also took an ATV tour and Valley of Fire with awesomeadventureguide.com. We had a great time on this tour, about 4 hours on the ATV in the dunes and than a drive through the Valley of Fire which is really amazing. I would also like to add that a drive through Red Rock Canyon is a must, it is only a five minute drive from the JW Marriott. Golf is excellent at the JW and I am sure the pool is amazing in the summer time. I highly recommend this hotel is you want to be away from the strip and experience more of the natural beauty in the area.	
