Dec 2 2007 	Great offstrip hotel	We were really pleased with our stay at the JW Las Vegas. You drive up to complimentary valet parking. Check in was quick and we assigned a room on the top floor which is only the 6th floor. This is not a high rise hotel.The casino (not run by Marriott) is nice and small with cheap tables. We enjoyed that very much since we are not heavy gamblers. The buffet at the casino is okay. We enjoyed the food at the Irish Pub although service can be sketchy.We were a little disappointed with the breakfast buffet in the hotel. Food was somewhat cold. Eggs were on the warmer too long. Stick to ordering from their menu. Service was good one day and somewhat unattentive the next day. Lorraine was great the first day. She offered great service. The second day the staff was more worried about setting up for a large party than the current diners. The large party took up more than a quarter of the dining room. That group should have been put in a meeting a banquet room.We did not use the pool because it was too cold. Bathrooms in rooms are as great as advertised. We will be coming more often to the JW Marriott in Las Vegas. This will be our 1st choice to stay every time!	
Nov 25 2007 	Nice off strip hotel to stay at.	Because this trip was with our children, ages 9 &amp; 11, we wanted to stay off strip to get away from the sheer numbers of people. If that is what you are looking for then this place is great. It was a beautiful property. The rooms were very clean, well appointed and quiet. I especially loved the bathroom. The only issues I had were that they don't advertise the restaurant attached to the casiino. We found it only when we were looking for Starbucks. We asked why and they said it is because it is not part of the Marriott but rather an independent operation. We ate at the hotels own restaurant once and while it was very good food, we are budget conscious and wanted something for less money when eating all meals out. The restaurant in the back of the casino had great food, a huge menu and very reasonable prices. Their breakfast was awesome. We spent most of our first few days looking for nearby Denny's or IHOPS when this place was right there only not advertised. The only other issue was that I think the pool should be open a bit later than 7 pm. Even 9 pm would be better. We felt the hotel was much more catering to the business traveler than families on a vacation but it should be the opposite since it is a resort and is very much for families. Overall we were very pleased with the hotel and service and would definitely stay here again.	
