Nov 23 2007	Excellent Guest and Meeting/Conference Experience	I attended a business conference at this resort, November 2  6, 2007, rate of $189/night. My transfer from the Las Vegas airport took about 20 minutes in pre-rush hour traffic. During the conference, all the attendees were transferred to the Strip, to the Mirage for dinner at Stacks and to see Love (Beatles Cirque de Soleil Show). That transfer only took 15 minutes. So, the Las Vegas Strip is a short transfer, but a transfer none the less. The JW Marriott is very nice with beautiful landscaping, a big resort pool, a big fitness center &amp; spa, its own casino, a handful of restaurants, a Starbucks, and a couple of shops. The rooms are top notch, spacious, and loaded up with marble bathrooms, separate tub and big walk in shower, a walk-in closet, safe, good desk with an Internet connection.From a conference/meeting perspective, it was just fine, with guest rooms comparable to Bellagio, Venetian, and almost at nice as the Four Seasons. So, if you are going to Las Vegas and dont want to stay on the Strip, then the JW Marriott will be just fine. For me though, given a choice, I would always rather stay on the Strip. There just a whole lot more to do and see, and you can avoid the transfer.	
