ngregated here and it was very fun. They have a very large waterfall that gives you a great sound. I heard they are building a water slide too. The housekeeping was outstanding and spoke English-which is not the norm elsewhere. They vacuumed up my diamond earring and actually took the time to take their vac apart and try to find it, which they did. I was so surprised and completely relieved. The bathroom tub was so nice and so big. Big enough for my whole family. I love the idea that they have fans in the bedrooms in that no place ever has these because they get unbalanced and are hard to service. The air rocked. We ordered room service most of the time and it was great. We ordered mac and cheese 4-5 times and they made it fresh and gourmet like for the kids. My husband went downstairs and ordered food from the fancy restaurants and brought it up for us to eat. We loved, loved loved the Spianni (sp?)Restaurant downstairs. I really thought it was a great deal for the quality and quantity of the food. We had take out from there 3 times and every time it was very flavorful and fresh. The chicken parm is very good and very Italian. There appetizers are sooo good. The bread is to die for.We had fish and chips at the Irish pub once and they were okay-the batter was bland. The sushi place downstairs had outstanding sushi. I heard the rest of the menu was not good at all. Starbucks pastries were incredible. I am usually not a fan of there pastries but these were super fresh and very unstarbuckies.The restaurant by the casino is outstanding for a cafe type place. Honestly, this was some of the best food in the hotel believe it or not. The service was incredible and the food even better.The food at the pool was not so great. The hamburger is pool quality meat.We gambled over at the Redrock, which is a very swanky hotel, and very fun to visit for a more Vegas feel. I love that they have a bowling alley and a movie theater. Plus the coolest thing is they have check in childcare so you can gamble or have a nice dinner. You must send in your kids shots records 3 weeks in advance so they can make sure everyone is covered since it is such an international clientele. There are tons of restaurants and shopping around the JW as well. I have been on tons of vacations and the amount of space this place provides with the quality of the service makes it a much go back to family vacation place in Vegas. Doing Vegas with kids would not be a good idea on the strip, but if you are okay with getting a sitter (ROSE with around the clock) then your time in Vegas can include both partyng and family time-Which is super rare! We did the Red rock drive to see the rocks and I hate to say it but it was a bunch of different colored rocks.The management of this place is on top of everything and made our stay very boutique like even though this place is very big. I say this in that everytime we turned around we were taken care of even without knowing we were platnium members and in the swanky suite that my daughter referred to as the &quot;castle&quot;	
