Sep 7 2006 	Terrific! Best of the Best!	Folks! I stay in hotels approximately 75 to 100 nights a year and last month took my family to Las Vegas and stayed at the JW for 3 nights. If you want to go to Paradise main land USA) this is the place. The rooms, grounds and staff of this hotel are first rate. A little history of the hotel will tell you why. This property started off as a Regent Hotel and for those world travelers who have stayed at Regent Properties you know they are Super Deluxe. When the Room occupancy % was below forecast the property owners brought Marriott in to manage the resort and Marriott has kept the standard set by the previous managment company. Yes there is a casino (Rampart) in the middle of the hotel (not owned or managed by Marriott) and it is a 50,000 sq ft intimate place to try your luck. In addition to the Marriott Restaurant Cerres there are a Casino Buffet, Casino Cafe, Irish Pub, Japanese Restaurant and a 24 hr Starbucks. I had previously read that this was Trip Advisor #1 Hotel in Las Vegas and it absolutely is. The LV strip is only 15 minutes away (visible from the grounds of the hotel) as is red Rock Canyon and the Red Rock Hotel and Casino. My advice is Stay at this Hotel!!!!!!!	
