Aug 8 2006 	Terrific stay at JW Marriott Las Vegas - Highly Recommended	We visited the JW Marriott Resort in Las Vegas recently for two nights to attend the wedding of our friends' daughter and also to visit cousins in Summerlin, the community within which the property is located. We found all the positive comments on this site to be true. The service was outstanding, everyone was very friendly - many hearty &quot;good mornings&quot; by the staff in the hallways. The valet parkers were cordial, fast and efficient. Our room in the Spa Tower was quite big, and the bed was one of the most comfortable you are going to find, with plenty of pillows and a beautiful duvet. All the furniture was fresh and in fine shape. Another nice feature was two bathrobes in the lighted walk-in closet (with safe) that were ready and waiting. There was also a convenient refrigerator that had free spring water, a rarity these days. It was clear that tremendous thought went into the design of even the smallest of things, such as the matching wicker trash cans, ice bucket and hamper in the bathroom.The bathroom was huge and featured a jacuzzi type soaking tub along with a separate shower enclosure offering a choice of a standard shower nozzle or a &quot;rainfall&quot; setting from above, which was great. The nozzles were both powerful and worked well. The rainfall was particularly enjoyable. For the person who wrote there were no washcloths, they are actually there on the bathroom counter, rolled up tastefully in the wood tray behind the complementary shampoo, conditioner, lotion, mouthwash, etc. While it took me a few moments to spot them, they are indeed there!The grounds are superb with water features everywhere, winding paths through the gardens, a great pool, palm trees - everything very well maintained. The wedding was held outdoors in a gorgeous lawn setting with gazebo type structure. We were impressed by the way the staff kept the event private, and then ushered us all into the beautiful Ceres restaurant overlooking waterfalls. All was taken care of professionally and in great taste. The service at the reception was impeccable, the wait staff was very friendly, and the food was delicious. The bride was beautiful, too!The surrounding community of Summerlin is booming and there are many new shops and restaurants very close to the hotel for off premises enjoyment. Boca Park is an example, just down the road. While US-95 (main access to downtown and the Strip) is being widened, it still worked fine for us and actually we enjoyed taking Charleston Blvd into the downtown area one morning to get a feel for the growth going on in the area. It took us less than 15 minutes to drive down to Bellagio on Saturday morning, and about the same time to return. This was our first time staying &quot;off the Strip&quot; and we found it a nice change of pace - very green, the JW is definitely a great place for relaxation. There is also the Aquae Sulis Spa that features about every kind of massage or treatment you can imagine, and had we the time, we might have given it a shot. All in all, this is a superb place to stay. One suggestion is to ask for a room with a balcony. While our room didn't have one, it didn't make a huge difference to us, I simply think it would be a nice touch and would allow even more light into the beautiful guest room. We would definitely return to the JW Marriott in the future.	
Aug 7 2006 	Hmmm... not sure this warrants all the over the top reviews	My husband and I are very frequent visitors to Las Vegas, we make about 4 trips per year and have stayed at just about every single hotel on the strip and a number off the strip as well. I was so incredibly curious about this hotel and property after reading the many over the top reviews on this site so we booked the hotel for our most recent stay. In any other city this would rate as a tremendous hotel but in Las Vegas where over the top seems to be the motto of the city I'd say this hotel is fairly marginal. The pool is nice but not out of the ordinary and actually quite small by Vegas standards. The service at the pool was also incredibly hit and miss. The room was nice but does not rival the standard rooms at The Wynn, Bellagio, Mandalay Bay, Paris or going off strip... The Green Valley Ranch Resort. I would say, however, that the bathroom does rival the opulent Vegas bathrooms on the strip and the tub is incredible. The grounds are beautiful, but again, doesn't quite rival The Wynn. As for the location, this is FAR off the strip, a 15 minute drive, much further than the better appointed Green Valley Ranch Resort is off the strip. The breakfast buffet is excellent. I would only recommend this hotel to visitors who are seeing family or in town for meetings that do not need to go anywhere near the gaming areas, for those visiting Vegas you might not be quite disappointed but you can do better staying at many other area hotel/casinos.	
