Aug 1 2006 	Wonderful Marriott	Wonderful, wonderful hotel. An oasis of calm in Vegas! Everything was perfect from check in until check out. Great choice if you have children as there is a super pool (only gripe was that it closed at 8pm) and it actually has a casino where children can walk through without being frowned at (unlike others we encountered in Vegas). Also a great choice if you are a golfer - two wonderful courses on the doorstep.	
Jul 29 2006 	It's true! JW Marriott is fabulous!	I love Vegas and one of the reasons why is the JW Marriott in Summerlin. Always one to stay on the Strip, I heard that the Spa at the JW Marriott was excellent (and I heard this while I was at Spa Mandalay, which I think is also an excellent Spa.) So my friends and I decided to stay at the JW Marriott to check it out. Both the Spa and the Resort itself were incredible. Spa first: excellent fitness facilties, fitness classes, treatments and lounge area. I had a body scrub and a clarifying facial and both were wonderful. Hotel and rooms: Who needs the Spa when the hotel room's bathroom has a large whirlpool jet tub in it, as well as a rainfall showerhead in the separately enclosed shower!!! FABULOUS!!! Bedding was soft and comfortable; room was nicely appointed, and yes...the bathroom is DIVINE! The hotel staff were always friendly, always professional, and always &quot;At Your Service&quot; when you needed extra anything (towels, robes, etc.) I was quite impressed when I received a follow-up call in my hotel room to make sure that my requests were met. There is also a casino so you really don't need to go anywhere else! AND, if you enjoy golf, there are plenty of beautiful, world-class golf courses surrounding the JW Marriott. Top-notch customer service will always win out, when you have so many comparable, hotels and resorts in one area. That's why the JW Marriott in Summerlin stands out as a class act from others. I stayed at THEHotel at Mandalay Bay the following day after the JW Marriott. Although the suite hotel is swank, the service at THEHotel was sub-par to the JW Marriott...no comparison! Give the JW Marriott a try...you will be glad you did.	
Jul 24 2006	Great resort - away from the Vegas Strip!	We stayed here on our way to Brian Head (UT). This is a great resort. We have stayed at many Marriott hotels, but this was even better than the &quot;usual&quot; Marriott themed hotels. The rooms are spacious (we had two queen beds) and the beds were very comfortable (down cover, really comfy pillows). We stayed in the &quot;Deluxe Guest Room&quot; which is the least expensive of all the rooms. We really liked the spacious bathrooms, and the whirlpool bath is separate from the shower. The pool area is nice - decent size pool and there are cabanas for rent. The resort is very quiet, since it's located in Summerlin, a bit west of the Vegas strip. It was perfect for us, but if you are looking for the &quot;Vegas strip&quot; experience, then you might not enjoy this place. We did not use the casinos, but we walked through it in the morning to go get breakfast. We are not really the &quot;gambling&quot; type so I did not notice much about the casinos. One thing to note: Since the resort is far from the strip, there are not too many restaurants located nearby, so we ended eating at the resort. We had purchased a &quot;family&quot; package which included a pizza/soda meal and a free movie selection, so the only meal we had to purchase was breakfast. The staff seemed very friendly. We would highly recommend this place to travelers, and we would stay here again.	
Jul 22 2006	Another enjoyable stay at JW Marriott	Every July my husband's employer schedules a conference at the JW Marriott. This is our fourth year at the resort, and every stay has been excellent. The hotel interior is beautifully decorated, and the grounds are beautifully landscaped. Everything is maintained at the highest level, and the staff is very helpful. The free shuttle to the Fashion Mall is handy, and the driver is quick to offer cold water to his riders -- very welcome in July! The only on-site restaurant we visited was the Promonade, where we took breakfast each morning. Really, the only negative about the resort is the long drive to the Strip to take in shows.	
Jul 19 2006	Gorgeous resort	We stayed at this hotel for 2 wonderful nights in July. The room was beautiful. Customer service was great. The pool is beautiful with water falls. I definately recommend this hotel. Quick drive to the strip or take the hotels free shuttle. I spent last part of the trip at the Venetian. Will definately stay at the JW if I have a chance again.	
Jul 17 2006	A Great Resort But...	...I do have a few minor complaints, which I will proceed to list before elaborating upon all the good qualities of the JW. First, where were the washcloths? None in the room, none at the spa. I could've used one to scrub away the stench of smoke from the adjacent Rampart Casino (REALLY smokey, even for a casino). Second, in the gym at the spa, there are no mirrors in the workout area, which makes weight-lifting a little more difficult. Also, the spa facilities, which are nice enough, don't compare with the spas at Mandalay Bay or the Bellagio.The room at the JW was great. It was more than large enough to accomodate the rollaway we requested which was delivered promptly and politely. The queen beds were very comfortable - some of the best hotel beds, comparable to Westin's heavenly bed, and better than the beds at The Bellagio, Venetian, MGM, et al. The mattress was the perfect firmness and the duvet and pillows were fluffy and comfortable. The bathroom was out of this world. In a city with numerous hotels boasting grand bathrooms, this one trumps them all. The jacuzzi tub easily accommodated two people, and the rainfall shower was very relaxing. Double-sinks and a separate room for the toilet made sharing the bathroom with four other people a little easier. Also, the faux balcony was a nice added bonus to an already terrific room. The whole room felt newly refurbished and showed no signs of wear, and the decor was understated and inviting.The pool area was easily accessed from the Spa Tower (where our room was located), and we were not forced to walk through the casino or a shopping promenade in our bathing suits. There were enough lounges for anyone who wanted one, and poolside food and drink service was friendly (not prompt, though our waitness apologized numerous times for the kitchen being backed up, and she did not get flustered when it took us a long time to order because some of us were on the other side of the pool). The pool water was unusually salty, but was cool and refreshing nonetheless.All in all, it was a very nice trip. The hotel is VERY calm and quiet - seemingly the antithesis of Las Vegas. We utilized the shuttle service a few times, but it would've been better if they had one later shuttle returning to the hotel, at least on weekends (11:30pm is the latest returning shuttle). Getting to and from the strip was not a problem, though a bit more action and better people-watching within walking distance (much better eye-candy at Mandalay, Bellagio, Hard Rock) would've been nice. Still, for the service, room, and pool, I highly recommend this hotel to others.	
