Jul 13 2006	Great time at the JW	Stayed the JW for a weekend getaway. Everything everyone else said was true. This is a wonderful place. The bed was one of the best I have ever slept in, very comfy. The bathroom is huge! The free valet parking was also nice. I only used it a few times though, because I mostly took the shuttle down to the strip. The shuttle only drops you at one spot, the Fashion Show Mall, down by the Wynn Hotel. So it is a bit of a walk to get down to the other hotels on the strip. There was one morning I took the shuttle down to the strip and there were only 3 or 4 or us on, so the driver kindly took us to whatever hotel we wanted to go to on the strip. This saved me quite a bit of walking, so it was much appreciated. The buffet in the hotel was only so-so. I did however like the food at the Promenade Cafe, very reasonable prices. I didn't use the pool on my stay, but I did walk by and it was quite crowded, and there was a lifeguard on duty, which was a pleasant surprise. As others have stated it is quite a bit out of the way of the strip. Plus the construction on the 95 makes it a mess getting down there. The hotel states there is a $9.95/day charge for hi-speed internet, but I was never charged for using it so another plus. Overall this is a great hotel, if you don't mind being away from the strip.	
