Jul 5 2006	Loved the JW	My family of 5 just returned from a 3 night stay here and we thought it was excellent. We wanted something off the strip that was still nice, and we got it. Check-in was quick and smooth, and the employees were very friendly. We had a room on the 6th floor w/ a balcony and 2 queens. The room was very clean, the beds comfortable, and the bathroom huge! My 6yr. old loved the big jacuzzi tub. We had a package that gave the kids pizza, soda, and a movie nightly and they loved it. We ordered room service 2 nights for all of us and the last night for the kids only. My husband and I ate at the Cheesecake Factory around the corner from the hotel. The food from room service was very good. We used the concierge service and found Mimi to be extremely helpful. She got us into Bobby Flay's Mesa Grill w/ no problem. We did some day trips from Vegas and yes, the traffic was a pain, but no worse than any other large city. The hotel itself is close to restaurants and some shopping. The resort is beautiful and we loved the pool. We were pleasantly surprised to see lifeguards there.  We would definitely return with or without the kids.	
Jul 4 2006	Loved the JW Marriott Las Vegas!	Stayed at the JW Marriott Las Vegas as the first part of an extended vacation around the Southwest that started around Memorial Day weekend. I knew the moment I checked in that this would be a hard act to follow! The resort was well appointed and the free parking was a nice touch. The room, however, was the best part of the place. It was huge! It had one of the nicest bathrooms I have ever seen at a hotel, with a huge rainbath shower that could probably fit four people and a large jacuzzi tub that fits two people comfortably. The room was also nicely appointed with a large, comfortable bed and tasteful furnishings (not as gaudy as The Venetian). The pool area is decent and was not crowded, although I believed the resort probably wasn't sold out based on the parking situation and their willingness to give a later check-out time. The main gym ($25/day) has a pretty nice spread of cardio machines and free weights but the real reason to spend that kind of money is to use the Spa attached to it which has a waterfall showers, steam room, sauna, cool plunge, and jacuzzi. Well worth the money. Also know that there is another smaller gym that is free in the case that you just want to work out but not pay the daily fee of the larger facility. Also ate at Spiedini (an italian restaurant in the resort) that was decent, especially when compared to the high prices for similar fare on the Strip. Yes, this resort is very spread out and it is pretty inconvienient to the Strip (on the map it looks close to the strip but the 95 Freeway is a BIG MESS at just about any hour and the surface streets aren't much better). However, for those that want a change of pace from the Strip and want to stay at a resort with great rooms and a slower pace, this is a great option. Would definitely stay here again.	
