Jun 23 2006	JW Marriott Las Vegas Resort and Spa Just OK	My husband and I just returned from the JW Marriott in Las Vegas. After reading all the great reviews, I must admit we were disappointed. Yes the rooms are large,but I felt the furniture other then the bed was a bit dated. The bed was quite comfortable. The layout of the room was large for the sake of being large. The little loveseat looked faded and only enough for one person to sit in comfortabley even though we are 2 small people and the chair next to it was not all that comfortable either. The colors of the room were just plain. The pool was nice and especially since there were so few people around. When we checked in we saw hardly anyone and felt we had the hotel to ourselves. I like a little more activity when I go to Las Vegas and this hotel is so far out of town I felt like we were in the suburbs instead of Las Vegas. It was just a little too quite for our taste. The road construction all over town also made it difficult to get to the strip. The joining casino was also quite. The food in the casino was very good and the restaurants were always empty. This room was $169 a night when you could stay at BELAGIO or Wynn for less. We also had a $1 a day phone charge put on our bill even though we never used the phone. In the future we will go back to the Strip and Belagio which we loved when we were in Vegas in April.	
