Apr 12 2006	Fabulous!	We just returned from a stay at the JW Marriott April 6-9, and we loved everything about it! We had a first floor room just off the lobby that had double french doors leading to a private patio with a small table and four chairs. It was so nice to sit out there in the morning and enjoy our coffee.The bathroom was huge, and beautiful, as mentioned by others. My husband loved the jacuzzi tub, and it was quiet enough that he could soak in it without even waking me up.The king sized bed was very comfortable. And there were two easy chairs as well as a desk with chair.My only minor complaint was the &quot;cooler&quot; fridge. For such a luxury hotel you would think they could put in a real fridge. I have never seen a cooler in a hotel room before. You had to stick an ice bucket in there to get any degree of coolness. The free water bottles were nice though.One of the best things about this hotel is the pool and the grounds. They are so lush and beautiful. You would think you were in Hawaii, not the desert. It was so nice to sit by the pool and let all your cares &amp; worries drain away. They have waitresses that come around often and you can order food or drinks. Ceres restaurant is very nice too, and is landscaped with waterfalls and palm trees outside. We had their breakfast buffet each day, and their made to order omelets and fresh waffles were very good. On our last day it was warm enough to eat breakfast out on the terrace and gaze at the waterfall. Priceless.We can hardly wait to go back next year, hopefully for longer.	
Apr 4 2006	Excellent experience at the JW	My girlfriend and I stayed at the JW Marriott from March 30 - April 2, 2006. Overall the experience was excellent and we will be returning.Upon our check in Thursday morning we were pleased to find that our room was already available. The front desk staff was excellent, very friendly and explained everything about the property. Robin, our bellhop, was extremely friendly and gracious and took us to a standard king non-smoking room (as requested) on the top floor. The view was good, with some rooftops of the casino and shops, but also could see the gardens and all of the nearby mountain ranges as well.But forget the view -- the room was absolutely incredible! First, the bathroom is easily the largest and nicest hotel bathroom I have ever experienced without staying in a suite. Two vanities, a 2 person whirlpool tub, all marble standup shower with a seat and rainfall showerhead, laundry bin, separate toilet room with telephone and even a ceiling speaker connected to the TV. The bathroom alone is about the size of many regular hotel rooms and is, in short, out of this world. Once you pass the bathroom, there is a walk in closet with digital safe and bathrobes, then a bar with glasses, ice bin and mini-fridge. After you pass the mini bar you will walk into the main bedroom area.The entire bedroom is stunning. Way oversized and decorated very tastefully in subdued gold tones with gold and black accessories. The carpet was a plush burbour and the room was big enough to have a couch and chair with coffee table as well as an oversized desk with two chairs, internet connection, and a TV that is much larger than most hotel TVs (not flatscreen, though). The bed was probably the most comfortable hotel bed I've ever slept in. Finally, there were the french doors. Forget the usual sealed off hotel windows, these were two oversized french doors that opened all the way onto a tiny balcony. Every night while getting ready we would open these up and enjoy the breeze.There were a couple minor annoyances: the paint in the hallway was scuffed in a few places, there was a spot on one part of the carpet, and it also turns out the fridge is actually a cooler, which was annoying. Overall these are minor issues since we felt like royalty in that room. We never wanted to leave.As for the rest of the hotel: First, the grounds are excellent. The pool situation is very nice. It is quite large, with two oversized 24-hour hot tubs, a poolside bar and restaurant, an adjacent sand volleyball court, and frequent cocktail service. It was not overrun with kids by any means and seemed to have plenty of lawn chairs for the taking. We never had a problem getting a seat and the hotel was full all weekend. We walked all around the hotel and were very impressed by how manicured the gardens were.The spa was also excellent. We had a couples massage, one hour long, for $236 including tip. The massage was excellent. The spa facility is very fancy but not stuffy, heavily staffed, and has like four pools in each locker room along with your standard sauna and steam. There is also an outdoor pool with special jets for your back to lay down in. Very nice. The workout room faces out onto the aerobics classroom and the private pool area and has really nice equipment with flat screen TVs. Highly reccommend the spa to anyone interested in that sort of thing. One drawback: if you don't have a treatment scheduled, it's 25 bucks per day to use it. The one big issue with this hotel is that it is 15-30 miunutes from the strip depending on traffic. The hotel offers a free shuttle every couple hours, but the last one leaves the strip around midnight -- so plan on taking a cab back ($40) if you want to stay out late with the rest of Vegas. But honestly, this could be the best thing about the hotel: you get the best of both worlds. We loved coming home to our amazing room at the JW away from the hustle and bustle of the strip. As for the casino and some of the restaurants surrounding it, this part of the facility was not up to par with the rest of the property. I learned that that part of the hotel is managed separately from the JW which explains its less-classy feel. It was certainly more of a locals casino and the food wasn't that great. Overall though, we will definitely be returning to this hotel. The hotel is not truly a five-star property, as it does not have some of the finer touches, especially in terms of incredible service, that one would expect from the Ritz or the Four Seasons. But it is certainly 4+ stars. The facility is excellent and the standard rooms are simply out of this world. Come to the JW Marriott and feel like a king. Hightly recommended!	
