 in Vegas.	
Mar 15 2006	Excellent Choice	I stayed at the JW Marriott on March 10 thru March 12, and I must say I was extremely impressed with the overall appearance, service, and value I received from the JW Marriott. I usually stay on The Strip when visiting Las Vegas (usually either at Ceasars Palace, or the Mirage), but had heard many wonderful things about the Marriott. The rooms were very large, with soft, warm down comforters and about five pillows on the bed. The bathrooms included two vanity sinks, extra large bath with whirlpool jets, and a wonderful rainfall shower. The hotel is located about 15 minutes from the strip, but offers a complementary shuttle to and from the strip that runs about 5-6 times over the course of the afternoon and evening. The casino is located away from the guest rooms, which is nice. There are several dining choices located with in the hotel. I ate at the Irish pub a couple of times and the food was great. Anyone who is looking for a great hotel located away from the hustle and bustle of the strip would be wise to give the J.W. Marriott a try.	
Mar 7 2006	Good Value for Different Vegas Experience	Stayed for family vacation. We rented 3 rooms. The hotel is great. Clean, well manicured, comfortable. The rooms are huge. The beds were better than any hotel beds I have slept in (and I've slept in a lot). Bathroom is huge with double vanity sinks and rain shower with separate jacuzzi tubs. All accessories are present. The rooms all have coolers but really could be replaced with fridges. Hotel Restaurant--Ceres--has an excellent brunch and is a great value. Also drank their one afternoon which was also great value. On the down side, the casino restaurants are not as good--especially the cafe. There are no tennis courts on the property (something that is very misleading if you look at the website). There is tons of golf around including TPC Canyons right across the street. Great location to Red Rock Canyon which has great hiking. Views of the golf course are the best. The courtyard views suck and the hotel doesn't acknowledge that. Also, the hotel chintzes out on really basic stuff. There is a nice gym in the spa but it costs $25. The hotel exercise room has one treadmill, one universal weight machine and one bike. The casino attached is not as big as the Vegas casinos, but is nice and accessible. No poker but most other table games.	
Feb 24 2006	What a hotel	My wife and I stayed Feb 17 to the 19th. The bed was very comfortable. The room, 3227, was clean and neat. Hotel staff were,5 star, friendly. Didn't have chance to use any of the amenties, golf, sauna,etc it was to cold. The grounds were kept clean. There wasn't even trash or cigg butts any where inside or outside of the hotel. They even have a 24 hour Starbuck's in the hotel,which my wife visited often. If you stay Monday it's steak night. The Sunday breakfast buffet was good. They had crab, omellettes, fruit, Champagne and much more for 14.00 a person. The only problem with the room was that the French doors looking out over the grounds leaked in cold air.Would I stay there again? Yes we are.	
