Nov 8 2005	Romantic and relaxing resort	My husband and I have recently returned from a three night stay at the JW Marriott and couldn't be happier with the experience. We had a late arrival on a Thursday night, and while they accidentally put us ina room with two queen beds (not what we reserved), they corrected it quickly and gave us the correct room on the 5th floor of the Spa Tower.The room was enormous, almost 600 square feet, with a very large marble-tiled bath (with a jacuzzi tub that could fit two and a rain fall shower), walk-in closet with safe, a mini-fridge with complimentary bottled water, EXCELLENT bed with top-quality linens, and truffles and mints on the bed to greet us. French doors opened to a view of the rocks and cascading water below, as well as the nearby golf course (one of several nearby) and the mountain range in the distance.We had a wonderful time at the casino, using the vast pool, booking a round of golf for my husband at the TPC-Canyons course (about $200.00, but much more reasonable than the Wynn on the Strip). The complimentary breakfast at the Ceres restaurant was excellent and the service was great. No one rushed us or shut anything down, even when we came in once close to the end of the breakfast period.Other activities included the drive through Red Rock Canyon and of course, visiting the Strip. This leads to the only slight negative - if you are planning to be on the Strip a lot, this is not the place for you, because of the traffic on 95, 15 and the Strip itself. If you can only take a bit of all that hoopla and want some relaxation, this is definitely the place to be.The staff was attentive (thanks, valets!), the landscaping, architecture, and decor was tasteful and lovely (fragrant plants, and no bad views out any window), the desk staff and concierge service was timely, friendly and helpful. I look forward to staying here again!	
