Sep 8 2005	A very nice hotel . . .	We have stayed at the JW Las Vegas several times. We have enjoyed it very much each time, and this trip was no exception.The grounds are lovely, yet convenient to shopping and restaurants. There are several restaurants on the property. The only one we ate at this trip was the Japanese restaurant and it was very good. We had a lovely suite. It was clean and luxurious, although not exceptional (hence the 4 stars rather than 5). Nevertheless, the room was lovely and comfortable, and the bathroom was exceptional with a large jacuzzi tub and a rain shower.The attached Ramparts Casino is not huge, but there are several tables as well as a wide variety of slots and video poker. It's seldom crowded or smokey. The much larger Suncoast Casino is right next door.If you are new to Las Vegas or love the lights and crowds, I would definitely not recommed the JW. If you have been to Vegas several times, however, you may enjoy the JW as a change of pace. It's easy to get to the strip as long as you are wise about when you travel. Non-rush hour travel to the strip takes about 15 minutes. Rush hour travel would take SIGNIFICANTLY longer.	
