Aug 6 2005	Beautiful Looking Poor Attitudes too uptight for Vegas	We stayed here during fourth of July weekend, we went because of Tripadvisors reviews and wanted to be away from the madness on the fourth of July down by the strip.First of all, the hotels appearance is all that they say it is, beautiful, fresh and clean. The attitudes, however, were very stiff and cold. We brought our two kids along, another reason we chose to stay here, seemed more family oriented and Vegas is running out of &quot;nice&quot; places for families to stay. It did not feel family oriented at all. We were stared at because our youngest is three. staff acted as if they couldnt believe children were there with us? There are a large number of older patrons, who frown on kiddies as well, we felt it all over, very uptight atmosphere. My husband is African and I am white, the racist glares from this place were hard to take at times. Usually, in Vegas, it's a place for everyone. The only place overrun by kiddies was the pool area. Beautiful pool, however, as a parent, beware of the cabanas, there are seedy individuals who rent them out (they are completly covered) and very adult activites going on in front of kids, as the doors sway open at times and you can see in. I did also complain about this to the managemnt, who responded promptly to me, said it happens all the time, but thanks for reporting it, but it was nearing the end of the day and the pool was going to close anyways, so I'm not sure what was actually done about it? We went to the hotels restaurant to have breakfast and we were the only ones there in line, place was nearly empty (we arrived late on purpose to get good seating) There were three workers there, ignored us for about ten minutes, as if we were invisible, then finally took the time to seat us. The waitress was rude and edgy. We ate and left feeling very uncomfortable. I couldnt believe all this, such a nice place with great reviews. I decided to reserve judgement and go to the casino, which you pretty much have to if you want to gamble, as it is far from the strip. It got worse. The dealer in front of me was openly arguing with her floor manager, YELLING in a foreign language, she was rude and angry, threw cards at me and had the worst of attitudes. then, when she saw I wasnt tipping her, She had the nerve of accusing me of handling the cards roughly?? Me? THats a first for me in ALL of Vegas! I know she was mad because I didnt tip her, who would? I got up to leave her table after I couldn't take it anymore. I complained to the hotel manager later, she claimed that the casino is contracted out to the Marriott and is not owned by the Marriott. Okay, but it's still in your hotel? She claimed she would give my entire room service tab to the casino to pay since they didnt know how to treat a guest properly. I was relieved and felt better over this. Until I got the bill, only one snack room service order had been removed, all else remained. Also, We felt it would okay to stay away from the strip, we had a vehicle, we drove in from L.A., so we figured we could just drive ourselves to the strip! Wrong! Traffic on the strip is unconceivably deadlocked, especially on holidays. We drove into town, took over two hours due to dead stop traffic, we got fed up and tired, so we turned back, all in all it took us roughly 4 HOURS to get to the strip and back to the hotel, and we didn't even get out of the car! Never again. Don't drive, use a taxi and be prepared to pay big bucks from this Marriott out ot the strip and back. They have a shuttle, goes to designated areas, it's timed and numbered, so with two kids in 125 degree heat, that wasn't an option.On the plus side, The bathroom rainshowers are great, the large in room T.V's are nice too. Also, I have to say the Irish pub is the nicest place in the hotel, classy yet very laid back, nice service, fantastic food, if only the entire place could be that way!	
Aug 6 2005	6 night stay	I stayed at JW for 6 nights with my husband and 2 kids. We had already stayed at the Wynn on the strip before we arrived here. We upgraded to a one bedroom suite for extra $60 on arrival and it was super, large balcony massive bathroom with double bath and huge shower, 2 tv's. I had no compaints about the room at all. The grounds are lovely with a nice pool.I found the hotel to be very quiet, hardly anyone around in the evenings and no entertainment especially for kids. The pool area is completely shaded before 6pm so we were looking for somthing to do in the evenings. We took the shuttle to the strip on one occasion and although the service is quick and free it only takes 20 people on a first come basis, so to make sure we would get on we turned up really early, the problem is that the line is outside and not comfortable having to wait when it is so hot, I think they should organise this a little better, maybe handing out a pass when you arrive so you could then sit inside in the cool. It is the same on the way back, the pick up point is outside Macy's (fashion show mall) which closes at 9pm so you must wait outside again.I am not sure that I would stay at this hotel again, yes it is lovely but there are fantastic hotels on the strip at the same room rate, the Venetian also has huge rooms. If you plan to go to Lake Mead or Hoover Dam it is better to stay at Lake Las Vegas, much closer and a really stunning area.No complaints about the hotel or service, I suppose it is just a matter of preference and if you are like me and spent 10 hours flying to Las Vegas then I would ratter stay on a classy hotel on the strip, you can always hire a car from there to see some other parts of Nevada.	
