Jul 27 2005	Great Stay at the J.W.	We stayed at the J.W. for three nights (July 22nd - 25th). The resort is beautiful - the rooms are large and the bathrooms are awesome, especially the tub and shower. The dining choices aren't wonderful, i.e. expensive, and there isn't a fast food court like many strip hotels, nor is there a kids camp, game room or an arcade for children. The casino is thick with smoke. The pool is nice, big and never crowded, however, it's salty. Valet parking is free and quick. We always received what we requested, i.e. extra towels, etc. from the front desk. It's a few minutes away from the hustle and bustle of the strip, which we love. However, I don't think the hotel is up to par with Four Seasons or Ritz Carlton - especially when it comes to kids. Luckily, we got a great deal.	
