Jul 5 2005	Not a fan of Vegas but loved the JW Marriott!!	My husband and I just returned from a Vegas trip during Memorial Day weekend and it was a wonderful experience! Our check in was smooth, the staff very helpful and welcoming. We were in town for business which happen to be on our 15th wedding anniversary! The management promptly brought champagne and strawberries to our room which was wonderful! The rooms are quite large as are the marble bathrooms with double sinks, over sized jacuzzi tub and full walk-in shower. I felt like I was in the Four Seasons Hotel! The bed was very comfortable and we even had a ceiling fan (not ususally seen in hotels)and a large walk-in closet. We did not have a great view, mostly the parking lot, but with some mountains in the background. Our first full day at the hotel, we had to track the cleaning/maid service down to make up our room (at 4pm!) but it was never a problem again. WE never ordered Room Service but we ate lunch at the small cafe by the lovely pool. It has great sandwiches and such and was reasonably priced. The Pool was absolutely beautiful and even though it was a holiday weekend, it never felt over crowded! A big plus for families...the pool staff has LIFEGUARDs on duty who responded promptly, professionally and quickly when a 3 year old slipped under the water out of view of his mother. No harm done, child was fine! As for the food, we did not visit any of the restaurants on site, some of which we heard are quite good. We did visit and loved that there was a Starbuck's Coffee on the property. The spa/fitness area is very nice. The equipment needs some updating, however.It is about a 15 min ride by cab or complimentary shuttle to the strip. Please note, however, that the hotel shuttle picks you up at Macy's on the strip. So if you are at MGM, you have to take a cab the 2+ miles to get the shuttle back to the hotel. They shuttle was always on time and the driver very friendly with complimentary COLD water for everyone on board! I would stay here again and I would bring my young daughters to enjoy this lovely resort-style hotel!	
Jun 30 2005 	Truly 5 stars	I was there for a conference and they ran out of regular rooms so instead I got a suite.Let's just say that the suite was so large, I actually had trouble finding my way back out.Aside from that, the hotel is very classy, a true 5 star. The last time I was in Las Vegas, I stayed at the Bellagio. I have to say that this hotel surpasses the Bellagio.It is pretty far from the strip so you will definitely need a car, or be interested in mostly playing golf.	
Jun 26 2005	A Real Vacation	After a few stays on the strip you'll find this hotel a totally relaxing place where you can have a real vacation. The location is in the beautiful and upscale planned community of Summerlin. If you want to go other places rent a car for $20. a day. Downtown is only a few miles. The strip is further, but it's all freeway getting there. The best part of my trip was playing in the Rampart Casino. It's a cozy place with great paying machines, good cash back, easy comps and good food. You won't find any place like this on the strip.	
Jun 21 2005	Nice Hotel but too far from the Strip	This Hotel is very nice, but the major problem is that it is too far from the strip. If you stay here, you end up spending approximately $80 daily on cabs. The complimentary shuttle is not practical since it is available only every two hours, you have to stand in line early since it fits only 20 people (if your number is 21 you are out of luck), and the latest shuttle leaves the strip at 11:30 pm (which is too early to go to sleep if you are on vacation).	
Jun 17 2005 	Very Very Enjoyable Stay	We just returned after a 4 day stay at the JW Marriott for business and pleasure. We loved our room--the beds were VERY comfortable--the best hotel bed I ever slept on, with cozy bedding. The carpets and wallpaper showed some wear in our room, however. The bathrooms were large; the water pressure under the rain-shower and the whirlpool were wonderful. Very enjoyable to use. Amenities in the bathroom were nice. Overall, it was very quiet and relaxing. The hotel was clean, well vacuumed, and smelled fresh. The pool was also refreshing; the water temperature just right. The poolside restaurant offered great sandwiches and drinks. Walkways outside were enjoyable, with palm trees, flowers, and water areas with small waterfalls. Almost all staff were attentive and hospitable. The restaurants and casino were great!Because the resort is so large, I think it needed more directional signs, even though a resort map is provided.	
Jun 12 2005	far from the frenzy but close enough to the action	This is a great hotel choice if you don't mind being 20 minutes away from the strip. It is an easy expressway drive to the strip and just minutes away from Red Rock Canyon. The rooms are fantastic with amazing whirlpool bathrooms and oversized rooms overlooking beautiful grounds. The casino was uncrowded and the dealers were really friendly unlike many strip casinos.The pit boss even was giving us advise on basic blackjack strategy! The restaurants were very good and the exercise facility was immense with just about every piece of equipment imaginable. My only gripe was that the massage services seemed assembly-line like. I felt rushed out afterwards because the next scheduled client was arriving in several minutes. I was able to utilize the whirlpools and sauna post-massage and that was wonderful. It was too cold to use the pool but it looked very nice. I will definitely be back. A room like this would cost 3 times as much on the strip!	
Jun 8 2005	Truly Five Stars	Very nice room, especially nice bath, beautiful grounds, attentive service ... we're fussy and we had not complaints. And, unlike many resorts, the restaurants are reasonably priced (though we also ate locally). Our one complaint is that if you don't want to spend $20 a day for the spa, the &quot;gym&quot; consists of two treadmills, a bicycle, and some weights. At least put an elliptical machine or two in!	
Jun 6 2005	Excellent alternative to strip hotels...	Having visitied Las Vegas 10 times over the last 7 years, I am pleased to advise we found that the JW Marriot in Summerlin was an excellent alternative to the strip hotels when we stayed for four nights over the memorial day weekend. We stayed in a very spacious junior suite (comfortable bed, wet bar, good view if you pick floors 5/6, rain shower and jacuzzi, good sitting area) and found the service excellent. The gym / spa and pool are all well equipped and the general atmosphere is far more peaceful, whilst still retaining all of the typical Las Vegas amenities and gambling options. They do run a shuttle bus although this can fill up and it only goes to the fashion show mall. Expect to pay between $30 and $40 for a cab from the strip including tip. For an alternative off-strip dining option, I recomend Rosemary's in Summerlin which is about 10 minutes drive away - the valets may even drop you off for a small tip. They have excellent top-end food and a comprehensive wine list - the wine is half-price Sundays and it is accordingly somewhat of an institution. We will stay at the Marriot again.	
