Apr 2 2005	Favorite spot in Vegas but...	Stayed here April 23-27. This was our 4th visit to the JW Mariott in under two years. With family in the area to visit, we've grown tired of the Strip, so this is an excellent choice to break free of the rat race. The spa and pool are phenomenal! A person can (and we did) spend most of the day there. Casino is much more enjoyable and quiet than the busy Strip spots. Sports book good also. Can't speak for the restaurants.Only problem with this place (and it's happened to us on two of our four visits) is when a smoker ends up in an adjacent room (on a non-smoking floor)--the smoke comes through the connecting door between the two rooms. We understand that a person could lie at the front desk and say they're a non-smoker when checking in (not the hotel's fault), but both times when reported to the front desk, they didn't seem too eager to do anything about the problem. So, like most anything else in Vegas, I guess it's just a crapshoot. JW staff, if you read this, PLEASE be more vigilant on this matter--some people (like us) are very sensitive to cigarette smoke, and the situation can ruin an otherwise great vacation.	
