Mar 22 2005	Was average.	My boyfriend and I stayed at the JW from the 19th to the 21st. The overall grounds were beautiful and well maintained and the staff were friendly enough. Our room was not as spectacular as I would have expected from the reviews and pictures but I think that may be due to the fact that we were staying in the Palms tower and it maybe older. We had a stain on our carpet and the room did not look as elegant and modern as the pictures from JW's website. Throughout the hotel the carpets seemed kind of old and worn. We paid $100/night through priceline and so our room was maybe a reflection of the price we paid. Had we paid the full price I would have been even less impressed. All things considered it wasn't bad. The casino was nothing special. The dealer I had for blackjack wasn't very friendly but I guess they don't have to be. They just need to be able to take the money right? Slots seemed tight. We spent a day at the spa and that was very pleasurable. We had a couples massage and took advantage of all the steam rooms/hot tubs/pools that the spa had to offer. This was most relaxing and melted our work stresses away. We enjoyed the Irish pub. There was no music when we were there but the food was good and the atmosphere is nice. Our last night (Sunday) we ate at the Japanese restaurant Shizen. Since it was Sunday (they said they get all there fish in on Monday) they were out of most kinds of sushi that we wanted so if you go do it early in the week. The morning of our flight we went to Ceres for breakfast. The hostess told us and everyone else who came in that the wait would be 10 min. Well we waited 45 minutes with no sign of a seat and still even as we left (we couldn't wait any longer or we would miss our flight) the hostess was still telling people that were coming in that it would be a 10 min wait. Needless to say we didn't have time to go elsewhere and so we went without breakfast. If she was at least honest about the wait we could have made other arrangments. I think this hotel would be great and affordable for families with small kids. We are in our early 30s w/o kids and found it to be kind of boring and a nuisance to drive the 20-30 min to get to the strip. Next time we are planning on staying at a hotel on the strip.	
Mar 18 2005	Very nice place but too far from the strip	Spent a long weekend there in February and really enjoyed the hotel and casino. The hotel was very clean, the rooms are very spacious and the bathrooms are wonderful (loved the very large jacuzzi tub). All the staff was courteous and helpful. Great selection of restaurants. Found that the casino dealers during the day were much more friendlier than the ones at night (spent 50% of our time at the craps tables). Pools are closed this time of year, they are not heated. did not use the free shuttle to the strip, we had a rental car. The complimentary vallet parking was fantastic. We had a wonderful time. The only downfall is that it is too far from the strip, probably 20 minutes and the traffic to get to the strip is horrible. Next time we will probably stay at a resort within 5 minutes of the strip.	
