Nov 9 2004	Head off the strip to the JW Marriott	Just got back from my 25th trip to Vegas (so you think I like this place?)! Stayed for the second time at the JW and it only gets better!Spent 3 nights in a junior suite and this hotel gets my 5 stars for one of the best hotels in Vegas. It's about a 20 minute ride to the strip so a rental car is a must, but having stayed at just about every major strip hotel it's a nice break from all the hustle and bustle that goes on inside of these hotels.For starters, you don't need to navigate through the casino maze to get to your room. In fact, the JW has 2 front desks. The main one in the Spa tower and another in the Palm tower. Having stayed in both my only suggestion is to ask for an upgrade to a suite in either tower though even the standard rooms rate better than strip counterparts such as The Mirage, Paris, Caesars, MGM, and Mandalay Bay.Big rooms, huge bathrooms with rain showers and the suites add a beautiful living room with wet bar and a hot tub in the bath.And the rooms are just the beginning. The grounds are spread out and beautifully landscaped like a tropical oasis with waterfalls and secluded grottos. Great pool area, never crowded and very few kids. Spa is probably second only to Canyon Ranch in the Venetian. Great food at the buffet (only open for lunch and dinner), along with one of the top Italian restaurants in all of Las Vegas and a nice little casino if you dont feel like venturing out to the strip.If youve travel to Vegas often, you owe it to yourself to stay at least once at the JW Marriott. Youll have a great time!	
