Sep 27 2004	Las Vegass Best Kept Secret	Normally I do not disclose to anyone the hotels that I like to stay in for fear that it would become too popular and ruin the atmosphere that drew me to stay there in the first place, but for the JW Marriott Las Vegas I will make an exception because I want the hotel to continue to keep up and continually provide the same quality service, so every time I stay there it would always be like the first time.I just got back from my vacation from the JW Marriott Las Vegas and again I had the best time staying at the hotel. I stayed in an average room with a balcony, but the room was as big as some of the suites I stayed in at other hotels. There is even a walk in closetnot a vanity closet that you get in other hotels. The room has a ceiling fan if you prefer a natural breeze instead of the cold air provided by the air conditioner. The bathroom is the best; it is all marbled with dual vanities, a large Jacuzzi tub, and a rain shower head. Men, this is the bathroom you wont be fighting for space with your significant other. You can do your manly deeds while she does her feminine treatments. This saves an awful lot of time.The grounds are impeccable with manicured lawns with lush tropical conifers, surrounded by koi ponds. We enjoyed just walking around the grounds admiring the serenity of the hotel. The pool is large and spacious in a semi-tropical setting. It was not crowded with sunbathers like you get at the strip hotels. The JW Marriott Las Vegas is after all a Resort &amp; Spa. So, there is always something to do for those wishing to leave the gambling behind from their quaint casino between the two towers. For golfers, I hear the courses are some of the best. If youre into a spa and massage, wait until you get a look at the spa facilities it is awesome to say the least. I used the spa exercise facility and I really worked up a sweat after eating all the good food from their buffet. Speaking of food, the buffet was very, very reasonable priced. There was enough diversity to even please the most discriminating pallets. We ate at the waterside caf for breakfast and sat outside close to the waterfalls. My girlfriend thoroughly enjoyed the romantic setting.I like staying at the JW Marriott Las Vegas because the lobby and the rooms are far away from the casino and you wont have to come down from your room hearing the loud noises and smell the smoke filled rooms like the casinos on the strip. I also like the fact it is away from the strip. I dont particularly like the crowds and the hustle and bustle of the strip. The JW Marriott Las Vegas is not only a great place to get away, but a wonderful place to bring your family.	
