Aug 7 2004	Garden of Eden in Sin City	My wife and I just returned from a 5 night stay at this hotel. It was a great place to stay. We wanted an opportunity to relax during the day and play at night. The &quot;strip&quot; has quite a few lovely hotels but as we toured it, we knew we picked the right place. The&quot;Strip&quot; is full of energy, has a lot of wonderful attractions, some great hotels &amp; has something for everyone from 8 to 80 except for...down time. If you are looking to party, hit the strip. I would recommend either the Venetian or the Bellagio simply in terms of ambiance although the skyline of NY NY hotel is something to be marveled at.. Quite frankly.. it IS cool. Be prepared for the sounds of slot machines and cigarette smoke hitting you in the face as your GOOD MORNING! But the Marriott has jazz playing in the hallways as you &quot;stroll the grounds&quot; waterfalls rushing from the lagoons situated all over the property with koi swimming in them. The valet service is free, doors are opened for you, service does appear to be a priority. The rooms are spacious, the beds comfortable, the bathrooms are AWESOME . The pool area is really nice, can certainly relax, although a &quot;kids pool&quot; would be nice. Kids have a right to have fun too, just find them their own area. Personally, I dropped mine off at camp =) We enjoyed having lunch at the Waterside cafe, which has &quot;grilled food&quot;, burgers, chicken salads, Full bar, etc. BTW, the nachos r awesome. The casino is adaquate, has everything you need, it is not a strip casino tho but again, serves the purpose. The dealers are friendly &amp; will help you with whatever you need. THe 24/7 resturant in the casino (think high end coffee shop) really comes in handy at all hours of the day and the food is good. . IF your there, ask for Janice. She was great ( and knows what machines to play!) All in all, we had a great time and would absolutely stay here again. AS a side note, on our next trip, I think I might spend 2 days on the strip and then the rest of my time here, as there is something to be said for being able to stumble back to your hotel room (Strip) rather than have to drive 15 min to get back to it. Again, Marriott = relaxation + resort feel and you just won't get that at any of the strip hotels. Good luck!!!!!!	
Aug 2 2004	good resort....	a real mixed bag...the hotel is very nice and has great amenities, especially the pool. The food was very good and the casino seemed just the right size. The service somewhat up and down. Upon check-in, I requested a room on an upper floor in the Spa Tower. The front desk staff didn't seem overly interested in trying to meet my request and offered me a 2nd fl room in the Palms. However, I did use the concierge service several times during my stay and they were on top of their game. They were always very courteous and accomodated any request. The distance from the Strip can be a plus or negative depending on your taste. It is a $30 cab ride each way, so if you are going to make more than a couple of trips, it can be expensive. This resort is definitely a good alternative to the hustle/bustle of the strip.	
Jul 25 2004	Quiet and away from the crowds	The JW Marriott is around 20 minutes from the strip out by a number of nice golf courses. The rooms are larger than average and well-appointed.Talk about a quiet and laid back place to stay. The pool is very large and we saw no more than 10 people out there on a weekend in the morning. The casino is smaller but has great gaming tables.Service is slow at the casino cafe and the food is just average. Otherwise the hotel staff was great and we enjoyed our stay.	
Jul 22 2004	This hotel does everything right.	My girlfriend and I stayed here on a recent weekend. The room was fantastic. Great bedding, huge bathroom, in-room safe etc. We spent two mornings at the pool which was large and well maintained with plenty of comfortable pool-side seating. If you have small children you'll appreciate that the hotel employs lifeguards. If you're a gambler, the casino has lots of low-limit table games (e.g. $5 double-deck blackjack) and good payout tables for video poker. We ate breakfast at the cafe next to the buffet and both the food and the service were excellent and fairly priced.If you visit in the summer I suggest making the 20-30 minute drive to the Mt. Charleston area. We did a couple of 2 mile hikes and the 80-degree sunny weather which was a nice break from the 105 heat of Vegas. The views of the Vegas valley are amazing.	
Jul 18 2004	Avoid the strip hustle and bustle!	This was a great change of pace to avoid the strip. It is located near the beautiful red rock canyon area so a rental car is a MUST for this location otherwise transporation to/from the airport will run about $35 one way. The service was excellent and the rooms are very large. This hotel grounds are beautifully landscaped and it is nice to strool through the courtyard after a long day and admire the views. We really liked to watch the young ducklings entertain as they explored the creek running through the property.	
Jun 22 2004	What a nice change of pace!	We were at JW Marriott from 6/6-6/10. We knew it was away from the strip, but thought we'd probably go to the Strip sometime during our stay. We did not. The hotel was lovely, the grounds impeccable, the pool uncrowded and very pleasant. We ate at all of the restaurants except for the buffet. The meals were priced very reasonably for what you got and they were all excellent. The casino had everything you needed, except for a poker parlor. The slots kept you playing ... my husband won $1,200 on a quarter machine and another $540 on another quarter machine. The blackjack tables had low minimums, $5-10, and dealt out of double decks instead of auto shuffling shoes like on the strip. I never left a blackjack table without more money than I sat down with. We walked everyday over to SunCoast and to the Boca Mall, which was a pleasant walk and had some very nice shops. We really did not feel the need to leave and go to the Strip. We will definitely return. I highly recommend it.	
Jun 14 2004	Great Hotel	We have stayed twice and look forward to our next visit.The spa is fabulous!	
Jun 11 2004	Superb Resort in Las Vegas	We've now stayed in three J.W. Marriott hotels (Miami, NY, Las Vegas). It's a terrific signature chain. The beds and linens are always great, and the rooms are large and well-appointed. The JW in Vegas is superb. Service was terrific. We liked it better than the Venetian, at which we stayed for our second night in town. The pool is huge! This is a classy joint, a great place to relax just outside of Vegas.	
May 24 2004	JW - Tranquil and lovely in NW Vegas	After reading many of the other posts and now having stayed a week, I have my own ideas about this resort. First the major plusses: it is very beautiful, well planned, lush, with a great pool. It is absolutely NOT crowded, even though the hotel is full. The prices in the restaurants are anything BUT expensive (lunch buffet 8.99 and better than anything on the Strip for twice the price - coffee show with everything under ten bucks - this place is cheap compared to the strip or even a regular kind of restaurant - and the food is very good), nice easy to navigate casino, incredibly nice front desk people, especially adria in the Palms tower - the rooms, while big, are very plain - but the jacuzzi tub in the very nice bathroom is a plus. . The negatives - if you are into action and having lots of entertainment options, this place is not for you. I loved hanging at the lovely pool, which is very large, with two big jacuzzi tubs. The lounge chairs aren't too comfy, but they are fine. There is a waitress taking orders, a nice grill at the pool and it is beautiful. You feel like you are in Hawaii. The room was large, but very plain. There were two beds, an office type desk with fast internet connection at 9.95 per day, great marble bathroom with small shower with rain showerhead, private toilet, and a great jacuzzi tub that filled fast and was great to lie in. The views are fine, but there are no balconies to speak of, just french doors that open up onto the view. Avoid third floor mountain view rooms because there is a concrete wall that goes half way up the window, blocking the view. Also avoid the rooms that face the Suncoast casino. they are building and there is a lot of construction noise. Try to get the rooms above the 30's. The hotel has two towers, and there is really no difference between one or the other. For food, there is the buffet, which is cheap and oustanding. The coffee shop is run of the mill, but very reasonable, and there is an Irish pub, Starbucks and an italian restaurant. They are all good and very reasonable. I can't imagine how anyone could say the restaurants here were pricey. That's ridiculous. They need to go to the strip and see what expensive is.You really need a car to stay here. They have shuttle service to the strip, but it is infrequent and doesn't go late except on weekends. They have free valet parking so its a breeze.The casino is perfect, not too big but with everything you'd want. I felt very rested and relaxed here, but when I wanted to just walk out onto the strip, that was not possible. It is very very quiet and tranquil here. Enjoy.	
May 23 2004	Perfect hotel/vacation but rent a car at the airport!!!!	We had the most Fabulous, near perfect vacation for our family and friends with a wedding we just hosted this weekend!!! The hotel was exceptional, the staff was friendly and accomodating, everything couldn't have been nicer... the only glitch for us all weekend was transporting family/guests who were hoping for either a hotel shuttle from the airport or for us to come back to the airport and get them... which wasn't convenient at all. Getting a rent a car makes it all easy... from cruising quickly (10-12) minutes to the strip for a show, getting to Fashion Show MAll or outlet malls for shopping, or just going 10 busy blocks away to the drug store, Cheesecake Factory, Euphoria Spa(nails, hair, makeup) or easy transport for any of the adjoining golf courses. or golfing etc. The hotel was flawless and the catering/wedding staff did an exceptional job for us!	
