Apr 14 2004	An oasis from the Strip-Love the JW Marriott!	The JW Marriott Las Vegas offers the finest room for the common man in the city. The Four Seasons floors at the Mandalay Bay does have the finest strip view. The JW rooms have nicer carpet, larger bathrooms, and walk-in closets. The Champagne Sunday brunch is ultra inexpensive and the best I have encountered in Las Vegas to date.	
Apr 13 2004	Fun and Romantic	I stayed at the JW Marriott 4/8/04 through 4/11/04. My girlfriend and I were celebrating our anniversary and I suggested we stay here. At first, she wasnt too sure that she wanted to stay here. The fact that most reviews say that this hotel is 15 minutes away from The Strip made us believe it was in the middle of nowhere. Being 15 minutes (or less) from The Strip ended up being one of the hotels best features. We have stayed at hotels on The Strip before, but as you all know, traffic can get pretty nasty throughout the day. Commuting to the different interest points from the JW was quite easy. Freeway access was nearby and traffic wasnt a problem for us considering it was the Easter weekend. When we first got there on Thursday, my girlfriends mouth literally dropped open when we caught a glimpse of the JW. The landscaping around the resort is absolutely beautiful. Palm trees decorate the entrance to the parking lot along with pretty little pink and white flowers. At night, the palm trees were lit up with rope lights, which made it look really nice. There was also a babbling brook with a small waterfall in the front of the resort. Absolutely beautiful! Being our first time there, we werent sure where we should go to check in, but the guys at the valet were very helpful and they pointed us in the right direction. As we walked in, two of the valet guys opened the doors for us and greeted us. Stepping into the JW for me was like stepping into a whole new world. It was like walking into my dream home. My girlfriend and I do not have a lot of money but we both agreed that we definitely got our moneys worth. We were able to book the JW for 3 nights for a total of $450. The lobby is absolutely lovely. There were chairs in front of a fireplace directly in front of us as we were walking in. I looked to the left and to the right and found more sitting areas, which really made the JW feel homelike. Once we reached the Concierge, Patricia, one of the JWs hostesses, greeted us. She was really polite and she really made us feel welcome. My boyfriend and I are in our early 20s and we did notice that most other people were in their mid-30s and up, but we didnt get treated any differently. We asked Patricia if we could have a room in the Spa Tower and she quickly honored our request. She told us she would give us a room on the 5th floor and it had a little balcony. She then gave us a map of the JWs amenities and handed us our room keys. The whole Check-In took under 10 minutes! The elevators were right around the corner from the concierge. We eagerly went up to the 5th floor to check out the room. The room was lovely! I went in and dropped my luggage and explored the room. My first stop was the bathroom. The marble floors and marble tile really blew me away! The Jacuzzi tub for two looked very inviting. Big mirrors surround the Jacuzzi. You can also play around with the light to create a well-lit bathroom or dim the lights for a more romantic setting. The towels that were sitting next to the Jacuzzi were neatly folded and had a little soapbox sitting on top of them. There was a tower rack with one towel next to the Jacuzzi. The standing shower has a glass door. In the shower you have the option of using the traditional showerhead or you can use the rainfall shower, which allows the water to come down from the ceiling and fall down directly on you. There were two sinks with a big mirror. There was also a lit, magnified make-up mirror. They also had neatly folded washcloths, with little bottles of mouthwash, shampoo, conditioner, body wash, and body lotion. Here we also found a little soapbox. There was also a hair dryer and a tissue box that had the tissue neatly folded into an accordion shape. There was another little decorative box, which could be used for storing other toiletries. Next to the hair dryer was another towel rack with two towels. Cupboards under the sinks were very spacious and a decorative trashcan was also under the sink. Room service was really good about taking out the trash and providing us with fresh towels every day. There is also a private toilet room, which also contains a phone inside. There was a volume control button within the bathroom to control the volume of the Surround Sound System. We also had a clothes hamper underneath another one of the towel racks. Next we found the walk in closet. We turned on the light inside the closet and checked it out. We found wooden hangers and two white terry bathrobes. On top of a shelf we found two extra pillows. There was an ironing board and an iron and they even had a bottle of water to be used exclusively with the iron. We also found a small sewing kit and a safe. There was also a garment rack ready for use. Moving on we found a little lit mirrored area where we found the coffee maker and gourmet coffees. Here we found 4 glasses ready to be used and we found a cooler. There was a full-length mirror on the wall next to the wooden armoire in which the TV was enclosed. In here we found a keyboard and a PlayStation controller. Next to the TV was a table with a Hotel Directory binder and a catalog with 2004s Best Hotels. There were two chairs next to the table. There were also plenty of electrical outlets available to be able charge our cell phones. The curtains were absolutely lovely because they allowed to create different mood settings as well. We had French Doors, which led out to the balcony. The balcony gave us a nice view of The Strip and of the golf course across the street. Back inside the room we found a comfortable chair, and a small loveseat next to a small wooden coffee table with 2 magazines. There was also a floor lamp behind the loveseat. We found two nightstands, one on each side of our King bed. Both had spacious drawers. There was a phone, a pen, and a notepad on one of the nightstands, and an alarm clock radio on the other side. The bed was neatly made and it had clean, thick linens. The thermostat was set to a comfortable 73 degrees. The room also had a ceiling fan and a ceiling lamp that had a dimmer. The room was absolutely lovely! We both agreed that this is the best hotel that we have ever stayed at! We didnt get a chance to use the spa or go to any of the shops and restaurants, but we did get a chance to check out the Rampart Casino. Payout is fairly good, and their staff is very friendly and helpful. One other area that we did get to check out was the pool. Walking out towards the pool area we just saw more beauty. There was a small pond with mini waterfalls with fish. On that Saturday afternoon we were able to see a garden wedding being set up. The bride and groom looked very happy, so I am considering finding out how much it is to have our wedding here too. The pool area was spectacular. There was a lifeguard on duty and they had plenty of fluffy towels to use. Lounge chairs were available all around the pool. There was a waterfall. Nearly the whole pool was 3 feet deep, and from what I saw its deepest was 4 feet. Cabanas were available for rental. I also saw two Jacuzzis, Im not sure if there were more. The Jacuzzis werent overly crowded. The only downside that I saw to the pool was the fact that it closes at 5pm. But oh well, rules are rules, and this wouldnt be an issue to not make me want to come back. I have to say that the valet guys were very courteous and helpful. When I would leave my car theyd give me my receipt quickly and on my way out theyd have my car ready for me within minutes and would help us with any bags. Theyd also open the doors to the car for us. Checkout of the hotel was also done in less than 10 minutes. Once again, our hostess was Patricia and she said she hoped we enjoyed our stay and wished us a safe trip home. I would highly recommend the JW to everyone who is looking for a fun and romantic stay in Vegas.	
