Mar 20 2004	Third stay; love it!	This was our third stay at JW. It continues to draw us back as the grounds and facilities are top notch. This trip was in mid-March.We again stayed in the Spa tower where the bathroom is spacious with marble everywhere. The rainfall shower is fantastic, and the jacuzzi tub can't be beat.To be sure, the place has its flaws, but they are minor. For example, our room with two queen beds, while roomy enough, lacked comfortable chairs or a couch. It came with a table and two standard chairs. There were a few chips on the furniture, but nothing to get upset about. The in-room coffeemaker was a nice plus.The pool area is fabulous and uncrowded. If you've ever stayed at a strip megaresort with a nice pool, you'll appreciate the lack of crowds.We did not find the traffic to and from the strip to be a major issue, but I'd advise avoiding rush hour as we saw some tie-ups on the freeway. With such a fantastic resort, there's little reason to go to the strip, except for the occasional show. If you've had your fill of the strip crowds, this would be an excellent choice. It also puts you close to Red Rock Conservation Area, which is a great side-trip.	
